full_text: This weekend’s summit was a critical milestone on a path toward a just peace in Ukraine. The U.S. will proudly walk with Ukraine along that path until Ukraine prevails and peace prevails. https://t.co/wiAZjyGIKE

I met with @Tsihanouskaya of Belarus to convey our steadfast support for the people of Belarus in their pursuit of a democratic future. We will continue to hold the Lukashenka regime to account and demand the release of political prisoners.

Today we raised the Hostage and Wrongful Detainee Flag at the White House in memory of Majd Kamalmaz. We extend our deepest condolences to his family and we thank them for their continued advocacy in support of securing the release of all Americans held around the world.

We are deeply concerned by the stabbing of U.S. citizens in Jilin City, China. Our team has been in touch with these Americans and our PRC counterparts to ensure that the victims’ needs are met, & appropriate law enforcement steps are being taken. We wish them a speedy recovery.

Saddened to learn an aircraft carrying Malawian VP Chilima and nine others has crashed. The United States offers our deepest condolences, stands by Malawi during this difficult time, and will continue to offer our resolute support in search and recovery operations.

Today I met with the families of Americans being held hostage by Hamas. I wanted to update them directly on the proposal that’s on the table right now that will bring their loved ones home and lead to a more secure Israel. As the President said last week, this deal must get done. https://t.co/fAIxOq1fFJ

One year ago, Quad Leaders met in Hiroshima and announced tangible benefits for our partners in the Indo-Pacific. Much progress has been made in the year since. We look forward to the next Summit later this year to continue advancing our shared vision for a free and open region. https://t.co/V0dGvcJzpO

Pleased to meet Paraguayan President @SantiPenap to advance shared economic, security, and democratic priorities. On behalf of @POTUS, I welcomed Paraguay’s support for democracy in Venezuela and condemnation of Russia’s war against Ukraine.
https://t.co/vckpnoRjmr https://t.co/lZOZset87U

Congratulations to @LawrenceWongst on becoming Singapore’s fourth prime minister.  Our strategic partnership with Singapore is as strong as ever.  We look forward to continued innovation and cooperation to promote a free and open Indo-Pacific.

The Georgian people are making their views known. Undeterred by intimidation tactics, tens of thousands of peaceful protestors turned out in rainy Tbilisi today to demand Georgian Dream withdraw the legislation.

We extend our deepest condolences to the families, loved ones, and communities of those who have been impacted by flooding and landslides in southern Brazil. We will continue supporting @LulaOficial's robust response to assist all Brazilians in these difficult times.

We extend our deepest condolences to the families, loved ones, and communities of those who have been impacted by the catastrophic flooding in Kenya over the past month. We offer our continued and resolute support to @WilliamsRuto and all Kenyans during the difficult days ahead.

We strongly condemn the death sentence for Iranian rapper Toomaj Salehi.  His voice amplifies the aspirations of the Iranian people and all those silenced by the regime.  We call for his immediate release.  #SaveToomaj.

I extend our deepest condolences to Pres. @WilliamsRuto, @kdfinfo, and all Kenyans on the loss of Chief of Defense Forces General Ogolla and other victims in a helicopter crash today. Gen. Ogolla was a key partner in our strategic relationship and we will miss working with him.

This morning, I spoke with my Israeli counterpart, National Security Advisor Hanegbi, to discuss events in the Middle East. During the call, I reiterated the United States’ ironclad commitment to the security of Israel.
The Uganda Court’s decision to uphold most aspects of the Anti-Homosexuality Act is deeply disappointing, imperils human rights, & jeopardizes economic prosperity for all Ugandans.

Honored to have Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Dr. Fuad Hussein back at the White House today to discuss further strengthening our partnership and to lay the groundwork for the important visit of Iraqi Prime Minister Mohammed Shia’a Al-Sudani next month.

Congratulations to President-elect @Prabowo on his victory in Indonesia’s presidential election.  As the world’s second- and third-largest democracies, we look forward to continued cooperation in support of ASEAN and a free and open Indo-Pacific.

I traveled to Kyiv today to meet with @ZelenskyyUa & @AndriyYermak to reaffirm the United States’ unwavering commitment to supporting Ukraine. We have stood by Ukraine’s side since this war began and will do so every step of the way until Ukraine has prevailed.
Was great talking with @AmbMonicaJuma today. We greatly appreciate Kenya’s commitment to bring relief to the people of Haiti and efforts to address current challenges in the Horn of Africa.
